CSC171 has the course title "Introduction to Computer Science".
CSC171 is a 4.0 credit course taught by Adam Purtee.
CSC171 is offered every Fall and Spring and Summer.
Hands-on introduction to programming using the Java programming language. Teaches fundamentals of programming and more advanced topics. Emphasizes algorithmic thinking and computational problem solving and provides an introduction to the concepts and methods used in Computer Science. Required for all CSC majors. STUDENTS MUST REGISTER FOR A WORKSHOP AND LAB WHEN REGISTERING FOR THE MAIN COURSE.
